##Don't forget, there are 10 million seniors

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Function description, every day a moving original true story.

With 112 days to go before the 2020 Gaokao, high school seniors are in the home stretch, delaying their return to school and causing the runners to stall. Fortunately, many schools open the network teaching, examinee people study at home, with self-control to overcome trepidation. At the crossroads of destiny, what are the candidates going through? How anxious and anxious were they?

He Yixiao, the first affiliated Middle School of Central China Normal University, senior three science students
Students are very upset, because the review materials are in the school
In early December, students in the class had discussed the case of unidentified pneumonia in Wuhan, which they thought was SARS. I followed it for a few days, and when I didn't hear anything new, I didn't care.
January 16,17, we have final examinations, the community has been on the news about the epidemic out. I had a cold at that time. After the exam, I found that I had a fever.
On the 18th, my father came to Wuhan on business. In the evening, he came to pick me up from school. My home in Xiaogan Hanchuan, my father worried that I stay in Wuhan is not safe, decided to take me home early.
I was sick the whole way, and I hadn't been in a car for a long time, so I felt a little nauseous. After an hour and a half of driving, around 9:00 p.m. , my father took me to the hospital in Hanchuan.
When I got out of the car, I felt much better. The doctor checked my blood, ruled out a viral cold, and sent me home without a prescription. At the time, doctors were simply putting on masks, and no special triage had been made for feverish patients.
When I got home, I was still terrified to see the number of people being diagnosed on the news. I went to bed at night with intermittent nightmares about pneumonia and waking up in the middle of the night.
During the Spring Festival, when learned that can not go back to school, to the online class, all students are very upset, because most of the review materials are left in the school. I also put the notes of the various subjects in the school, which I have collated since the knowledge points and wrong questions, I used to review notes before every exam. Now the book is not at hand, if the reorganization will be very troublesome.
Taking an online class
Now I have to do all the printing myself. We have a printer at home. I'll print out the test. Other students home if there is no printer, can only look at the information on the computer while doing the problem, will be more trouble. I know that there are more and more students of the same age taking online courses in the country. I think if someone goes back to their hometown, or there is no internet or computer in their home, it will affect their study efficiency even more.
There are still about 100 days to go before the college entrance examination. I should study every day at this time, but when I stay at home, I can't stop playing with my mobile phone and want to relax.
I like Shanghai very much, the goal which sets for oneself is Fudan or Jiao Tong University, wants to study and the biology related specialty. I'm very interested in all kinds of animals and plants, and, on the other hand, to protect living things is to protect people, like this bat.
Wild animals may carry the virus, but it is usually very unlikely to be transmitted to humans. However, if every day someone eats wild animals, countless accidental accumulation of these viruses into human society is inevitable. Seventeen years later, we still have not learned the lessons of SARS.
I like watching popular science videos made by bloggers on Youtube. I saw a video of a nonprofit organization in Africa dedicated to protecting and treating pangolins, where people and Pangolins are as friends as we are with cats and dogs. Pangolins are still used as food and medicine in China, and by the most conservative estimates, 10,000 are illegally trafficked into the country each year. I think it's a pity that pangolins are now endangered. When I'm more capable, I also want to make some popular science videos, which appeal to the public to protect animals.
It's not so much about protecting them as it is about trying to minimize the harm that people do to them. One theory is that humans are the most dangerous virus to other organisms on the planet. In a way, it is. After all, viruses can not destroy a species completely, but humans can.

Syncline, the first affiliated Middle School of Central China Normal University, senior three liberal arts students
When I was anxious, I did tests to calm myself down

On January 20, I was checking my Weibo account during my lunch break and saw "one new death from coronavirus pneumonia in Wuhan" and "17 new cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan" on the hot search site.
When I returned to school in the afternoon, one-third of the class wore masks. The student said that at noon that day, the N95 mask of the off-campus convenience store had already marked a price of 40 yuan.
Second period in the afternoon, we are having a geography lesson. In the middle of the class, the head teacher suddenly opened the door and informed us that due to the Wuhan COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, we had been asked by the Education Bureau to take an early holiday, students whose families live in other provinces and cities can stay another night at most and must return home the next day.
I'm both happy and upset about the early holiday. At that time, we are still optimistic, the students joked: "In case of a serious epidemic, we do not have to return to school on time. " When I returned home, I only took the books to write winter vacation homework, who did not expect a short period of time will not be back to school.
On January 22, twenty-eight of the lunar calendar, my father was on his way home from Chongqing to celebrate the Lunar New Year. At night, I heard him coughing, and I was scared. I wish my dad would go to the hospital for a check-up, but my mom says going to the hospital at this time can lead to cross-infection. We had an argument about it, but luckily dad was okay.
On January 23rd, the city of Wuhan was declared closed. All afternoon, I watched Weibo. Some people on the Internet to Wuhan people open a map cannon, "selfish" , "zombies" , "mouth" , I see will not help but burn back. It is infuriating to judge a group by the actions of individuals.
January 27, I received a notice in the class QQ group, delayed back to school, senior three students on the sixth day of the New Year formal class, and changed to live online teaching. According to the school schedule, the teacher on the network live lectures, six classes a day, three classes a day, from 8:30 in the morning to 4:00 in the afternoon, at night time self-study, the teachers in the Qq Group answer questions.
The flip side of a history teacher

A lot of interesting things happened during the live lecture. Our math teacher was stuck in the country, and he was forced to go live next door to the Wi fi network, which was constantly buzzing with the sound of chickens. The political teacher in the next class, who answered questions by name through a lucky draw, drew himself History teacher and head teacher in the group issued a notice to call us "love Qing" , we like to reply him "something" , "promise" .
Another Day, I wrote to my geography teacher and asked, "why didn't the green car become a streamlined front? " She replied that I should ask the physics teacher and showed my teeth three times, it was a striking contrast to her usual image of gentleness, poise, and modesty.
I cut back on the social news. Every time I feel anxious, I will write the paper to calm myself.
At present, I get up at 8 o'clock in the morning, 1 or 2 o'clock in the morning, do two sets of papers every day, a set of math, a set of English, but also practice Wen comprehensive multiple choice questions. Most of the students did not bring back their books and review materials, so the teacher sent the electronic version to the class group. My printer broke down, I usually like to draw, bought a digital board, this time directly with a digital board on the computer to write papers. Every day in front of the screen study, the eye is particularly uncomfortable.
This period of time, I have a lot of students to show later want to take an examination of the idea of the civil service. Perhaps because they want their voices not to be ignored, they want to gain power to change society, not just on the Internet "incompetent rage. ".
I admire their ambition of "standing up for the world, standing up for the people" , but I feel that expressing views on the Internet is also a way to participate in the social process, as well as the civil service exam.

Cheung Lok Lok Wuhan No. 4 Secondary School, senior 3-year anchor
I am the national examination of the last division students, there is no repeat opportunity
The GAOKAO is only 112 days away. I was supposed to take the second-round exam of Zhejiang Media College in February, but it has been postponed. The new exam time is still waiting for the announcement.

I really want to go back to school, and I hope we can get back to class as soon as possible.
Hubei Province uses the National College entrance examination. Next year, the national examination paper will implement the "3 + 2 + 1" model, that is, the three unified subjects language, mathematics, foreign languages, "2" is in politics, geography, chemistry, Biology 4 Optional 2, "1" is a choice between physics and history.
This means that we are the last college entrance examination reform of Liberal Arts and science students, so there is no way out. To this end, most of the students in the class are very anxious, we attach great importance to every simulation test results, when the results are not good will suddenly anxiety, serious when crying. We are the Wuhan examinee, before the university entrance examination also caught the suspension, the life is ill-fated.
January 20 at 8:30 pm, we are on the evening of self-study, suddenly the teacher came in notice early holiday. He didn't specify the reason, but the students knew it. During that time, the number of people infected increased dramatically, the situation became more and more serious, and other schools had already closed early.
Back home, we in the class group turn some relevant information, we are very anxious. A classmate at the same school, home of the elderly sick, unable to contact the bed, his isolation at home. He posted a request for help on myspace and Weibo, and many of his classmates forwarded it to him.
On February 1, the school announced that back-to-school classes would be held online, with each subject teacher setting up their own qq group of subjects and assigning their own study tasks. These days down, I think, the effect of live-streaming class than in school much worse. The home is too comfortable, the temptation is too much, I am not very conscious self-discipline, recently even life is very chaotic. In addition, the teacher and students communication is not convenient, some problems through the typing is difficult to explain clearly, the teacher when the efficiency is low.
Photo | happy desk
Last year, on November 28, I finished 25 days of training, December 19, to participate in Hubei Province, January 15, I went to Changsha test site to participate in the Zhejiang Media College entrance examination. I was quite satisfied with the results of the art examination. I had planned to spend the next few days in school to make up for my "fatal weakness" . My Weak Foundation, the original plan to take the art examination in February, after the beginning of March to find a teacher one-on-one tutorial, a week make up twice. But for now, we'll have to wait until the special period is over.

Li Xiaowen, Wuhan Hongshan Middle School, senior three science students
Home-schooled in Ortho, wanted to study medicine
After my senior year of high school, I checked my medical school grades and found that if I didn't work harder, I probably wouldn't get into medical school. If I don't go into medicine, I'll regret it for the rest of my life. So, I spent more time on my study. Facing the difficult problem must understand, I am afraid because of a little knowledge in the college entrance examination lost points.
One night when I was in the fifth grade, my father was on a business trip. My mother suddenly felt unwell. She had palpitations, dizziness and could not walk. I was scared. We were the only two people at home, I helped my mother out the door, take a taxi to the hospital.
I still remember how scared I was, the first time I realized that a loved one might suddenly leave. When I got to the hospital, emergency physician arranged for my mother to be examined and told us it was just hypokalemia, I was relieved.
I used to think that if I had known medicine, maybe I could have helped my mother, and I wouldn't have been so helpless and scared. In Times of crisis, the help that doctors give to their patients is very powerful.
When I was in junior high school, I liked the Korean actor Lee Jong-seok because he watched the Korean drama Doctor from another country. In which he plays a heart surgeon with superpowers, saving lives in the first line, especially handsome. Gradually, I became fascinated by the medical profession. Next, I looked at many medical-related movies and TV shows, starting with the more idealistic and romantic ones, unnatural death, Grey's Anatomy, and later, more realistic medical documentaries, such as the world and the Chinese doctor.
I've come to understand that doctors have a bright side, but they also have a dark side. Too often, there are few things a doctor can do -- costs, family wishes, medical resources -- all within limits. I learned that I wanted to study medicine, although my mother expressed concern, friends have discouraged me. None of this dissuaded me from studying medicine.
This year, I switched to an online course, and the homeschooling method is more suitable for me. I am a bit partial, math is not good, in school, all the time is arranged, what class to do what, sometimes I want to use the language and English time to write math, the teacher always said.
Image | Li Xiaowen's desk
At home, I can allocate my time according to my study situation. For example, write a math paper in the morning when you're at your best, and then recite the liberal arts when you're relaxed. It's just that staring at a screen all day isn't good for your eyes or your neck.
I saw a video on the Internet, someone asked a retired old doctor, so old, why still voluntarily on the line, not afraid of infection? She replied, "as a medical warrior, to die in battle is a good death. " I was moved to tears by the words.
Whether it is Dr Yang Wen, Dr Tao Yong or Dr Li Wenliang, I believe that what happens to them is a constant risk for every doctor; they show kindness and purity even when they are in danger, i believe this is what the medical profession is all about.
Instead of repelling me, what happened to these doctors made me see their value proposition. Tao Yong, an ophthalmologist, posted a post before he was stabbed, quoting Dr. Trudo's Epitaph: "sometimes healed, often helped, always comforted. ". I hope I can get into the Southern Medical University, and like him, become a doctor who can care for patients.
When I'm tired, I check my twitter feed. Seeing doctors from all over the country come to support Wuhan, I gained the motivation to study again. On the Internet, more and more people pay attention to the doctor's treatment, speak up for them, I also like to see fire.
In the future, I want to be part of the doctor community.

I saw a video of a nonprofit organization in Africa dedicated to protecting and treating pangolins, where people and Pangolins are as friends as we are with cats and dogs. Pangolins are still used as food and medicine in China, and by the most conservative estimates, 10,000 are illegally trafficked into the country each year. I think it's a pity that pangolins are now endangered. When I'm more capable, I also want to make some popular science videos, which appeal to the public to protect animals.
It's not so much about protecting them as it is about trying to minimize the harm that people do to them. One theory is that humans are the most dangerous virus to other organisms on the planet. In a way, it is. After all, viruses can not destroy a species completely, but humans can.

He Yixiao, the first affiliated Middle School of Central China Normal University, senior three science students

Students are very upset, because the review materials are in the school
In early December, students in the class had discussed the case of unidentified pneumonia in Wuhan, which they thought was SARS. I followed it for a few days, and when I didn't hear anything new, I didn't care.
January 16,17, we have final examinations, the community has been on the news about the epidemic out. I had a cold at that time. After the exam, I found that I had a fever.
On the 18th, my father came to Wuhan on business. In the evening, he came to pick me up from school. My home in Xiaogan Hanchuan, my father worried that I stay in Wuhan is not safe, decided to take me home early.
I was sick the whole way, and I hadn't been in a car for a long time, so I felt a little nauseous. After an hour and a half of driving, around 9:00 p.m. , my father took me to the hospital in Hanchuan.
When I got out of the car, I felt much better. The doctor checked my blood, ruled out a viral cold, and sent me home without a prescription. At the time, doctors were simply putting on masks, and no special triage had been made for feverish patients.
When I got home, I was still terrified to see the number of people being diagnosed on the news. I went to bed at night with intermittent nightmares about pneumonia and waking up in the middle of the night.
During the Spring Festival, when learned that can not go back to school, to the online class, all students are very upset, because most of the review materials are left in the school. I also put the notes of the various subjects in the school, which I have collated since the knowledge points and wrong questions, I used to review notes before every exam. Now the book is not at hand, if the reorganization will be very troublesome.
Taking an online class

When I returned to school in the afternoon, one-third of the class wore masks. The student said that at noon that day, the N95 mask of the off-campus convenience store had already marked a price of 40 yuan.
Second period in the afternoon, we are having a geography lesson. In the middle of the class, the head teacher suddenly opened the door and informed us that due to the Wuhan COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, we had been asked by the Education Bureau to take an early holiday, students whose families live in other provinces and cities can stay another night at most and must return home the next day.
I'm both happy and upset about the early holiday. At that time, we are still optimistic, the students joked: "In case of a serious epidemic, we do not have to return to school on time. " When I returned home, I only took the books to write winter vacation homework, who did not expect a short period of time will not be back to school.
On January 22, twenty-eight of the lunar calendar, my father was on his way home from Chongqing to celebrate the Lunar New Year. At night, I heard him coughing, and I was scared. I wish my dad would go to the hospital for a check-up, but my mom says going to the hospital at this time can lead to cross-infection. We had an argument about it, but luckily dad was okay.
On January 23rd, the city of Wuhan was declared closed. All afternoon, I watched Weibo. Some people on the Internet to Wuhan people open a map cannon, "selfish" , "zombies" , "mouth" , I see will not help but burn back. It is infuriating to judge a group by the actions of individuals.
January 27, I received a notice in the class QQ group, delayed back to school, senior three students on the sixth day of the New Year formal class, and changed to live online teaching. According to the school schedule, the teacher on the network live lectures, six classes a day, three classes a day, from 8:30 in the morning to 4:00 in the afternoon, at night time self-study, the teachers in the Qq Group answer questions.
The flip side of a history teacher

A lot of interesting things happened during the live lecture. Our math teacher was stuck in the country, and he was forced to go live next door to the Wi fi network, which was constantly buzzing with the sound of chickens. The political teacher in the next class, who answered questions by name through a lucky draw, drew himself History teacher and head teacher in the group issued a notice to call us "love Qing" , we like to reply him "something" , "promise" .
Another Day, I wrote to my geography teacher and asked, "why didn't the green car become a streamlined front? " She replied that I should ask the physics teacher and showed my teeth three times, it was a striking contrast to her usual image of gentleness, poise, and modesty.
I cut back on the social news. Every time I feel anxious, I will write the paper to calm myself.
At present, I get up at 8 o'clock in the morning, 1 or 2 o'clock in the morning, do two sets of papers every day, a set of math, a set of English, but also practice Wen comprehensive multiple choice questions. Most of the students did not bring back their books and review materials, so the teacher sent the electronic version to the class group. My printer broke down, I usually like to draw, bought a digital board, this time directly with a digital board on the computer to write papers. Every day in front of the screen study, the eye is particularly uncomfortable.
This period of time, I have a lot of students to show later want to take an examination of the idea of the civil service. Perhaps because they want their voices not to be ignored, they want to gain power to change society, not just on the Internet "incompetent rage. ".
I admire their ambition of "standing up for the world, standing up for the people" , but I feel that expressing views on the Internet is also a way to participate in the social process, as well as the civil service exam.

Back home, we in the class group turn some relevant information, we are very anxious. A classmate at the same school, home of the elderly sick, unable to contact the bed, his isolation at home. He posted a request for help on myspace and Weibo, and many of his classmates forwarded it to him.

These days down, I think, the effect of live-streaming class than in school much worse. The home is too comfortable, the temptation is too much, I am not very conscious self-discipline, recently even life is very chaotic. In addition, the teacher and students communication is not convenient, some problems through the typing is difficult to explain clearly, the teacher when the efficiency is low.

Li Xiaowen, Wuhan Hongshan Middle School, senior three science students
Home-schooled in Ortho, wanted to study medicine
After my senior year of high school, I checked my medical school grades and found that if I didn't work harder, I probably wouldn't get into medical school. If I don't go into medicine, I'll regret it for the rest of my life. So, I spent more time on my study. Facing the difficult problem must understand, I am afraid because of a little knowledge in the college entrance examination lost points.
One night when I was in the fifth grade, my father was on a business trip. My mother suddenly felt unwell. She had palpitations, dizziness and could not walk. I was scared. We were the only two people at home, I helped my mother out the door, take a taxi to the hospital.
I still remember how scared I was, the first time I realized that a loved one might suddenly leave. When I got to the hospital, emergency physician arranged for my mother to be examined and told us it was just hypokalemia, I was relieved.
I used to think that if I had known medicine, maybe I could have helped my mother, and I wouldn't have been so helpless and scared. In Times of crisis, the help that doctors give to their patients is very powerful.
When I was in junior high school, I liked the Korean actor Lee Jong-seok because he watched the Korean drama Doctor from another country. In which he plays a heart surgeon with superpowers, saving lives in the first line, especially handsome. Gradually, I became fascinated by the medical profession. Next, I looked at many medical-related movies and TV shows, starting with the more idealistic and romantic ones, unnatural death, Grey's Anatomy, and later, more realistic medical documentaries, such as the world and the Chinese doctor.
I've come to understand that doctors have a bright side, but they also have a dark side. Too often, there are few things a doctor can do -- costs, family wishes, medical resources -- all within limits. I learned that I wanted to study medicine, although my mother expressed concern, friends have discouraged me. None of this dissuaded me from studying medicine.
This year, I switched to an online course, and the homeschooling method is more suitable for me. I am a bit partial, math is not good, in school, all the time is arranged, what class to do what, sometimes I want to use the language and English time to write math, the teacher always said.
Image | Li Xiaowen's desk
At home, I can allocate my time according to my study situation. For example, write a math paper in the morning when you're at your best, and then recite the liberal arts when you're relaxed. It's just that staring at a screen all day isn't good for your eyes or your neck.
I saw a video on the Internet, someone asked a retired old doctor, so old, why still voluntarily on the line, not afraid of infection? She replied, "as a medical warrior, to die in battle is a good death. " I was moved to tears by the words.
Whether it is Dr Yang Wen, Dr Tao Yong or Dr Li Wenliang, I believe that what happens to them is a constant risk for every doctor; they show kindness and purity even when they are in danger, i believe this is what the medical profession is all about.
Instead of repelling me, what happened to these doctors made me see their value proposition. Tao Yong, an ophthalmologist, posted a post before he was stabbed, quoting Dr. Trudo's Epitaph: "sometimes healed, often helped, always comforted. ". I hope I can get into the Southern Medical University, and like him, become a doctor who can care for patients.
When I'm tired, I check my twitter feed. Seeing doctors from all over the country come to support Wuhan, I gained the motivation to study again. On the Internet, more and more people pay attention to the doctor's treatment, speak up for them, I also like to see fire.
In the future, I want to be part of the doctor community.

Li Xiaowen, Wuhan Hongshan Middle School, senior three science students

Home-schooled in Ortho, wanted to study medicine
After my senior year of high school, I checked my medical school grades and found that if I didn't work harder, I probably wouldn't get into medical school. If I don't go into medicine, I'll regret it for the rest of my life. So, I spent more time on my study. Facing the difficult problem must understand, I am afraid because of a little knowledge in the college entrance examination lost points.
One night when I was in the fifth grade, my father was on a business trip. My mother suddenly felt unwell. She had palpitations, dizziness and could not walk. I was scared. We were the only two people at home, I helped my mother out the door, take a taxi to the hospital.
I still remember how scared I was, the first time I realized that a loved one might suddenly leave. When I got to the hospital, emergency physician arranged for my mother to be examined and told us it was just hypokalemia, I was relieved.
I used to think that if I had known medicine, maybe I could have helped my mother, and I wouldn't have been so helpless and scared. In Times of crisis, the help that doctors give to their patients is very powerful.
When I was in junior high school, I liked the Korean actor Lee Jong-seok because he watched the Korean drama Doctor from another country. In which he plays a heart surgeon with superpowers, saving lives in the first line, especially handsome. Gradually, I became fascinated by the medical profession. Next, I looked at many medical-related movies and TV shows, starting with the more idealistic and romantic ones, unnatural death, Grey's Anatomy, and later, more realistic medical documentaries, such as the world and the Chinese doctor.
I've come to understand that doctors have a bright side, but they also have a dark side. Too often, there are few things a doctor can do -- costs, family wishes, medical resources -- all within limits. I learned that I wanted to study medicine, although my mother expressed concern, friends have discouraged me. None of this dissuaded me from studying medicine.
This year, I switched to an online course, and the homeschooling method is more suitable for me. I am a bit partial, math is not good, in school, all the time is arranged, what class to do what, sometimes I want to use the language and English time to write math, the teacher always said.
Image | Li Xiaowen's desk
At home, I can allocate my time according to my study situation. For example, write a math paper in the morning when you're at your best, and then recite the liberal arts when you're relaxed. It's just that staring at a screen all day isn't good for your eyes or your neck.
I saw a video on the Internet, someone asked a retired old doctor, so old, why still voluntarily on the line, not afraid of infection? She replied, "as a medical warrior, to die in battle is a good death. " I was moved to tears by the words.
Whether it is Dr Yang Wen, Dr Tao Yong or Dr Li Wenliang, I believe that what happens to them is a constant risk for every doctor; they show kindness and purity even when they are in danger, i believe this is what the medical profession is all about.
Instead of repelling me, what happened to these doctors made me see their value proposition. Tao Yong, an ophthalmologist, posted a post before he was stabbed, quoting Dr. Trudo's Epitaph: "sometimes healed, often helped, always comforted. ". I hope I can get into the Southern Medical University, and like him, become a doctor who can care for patients.
When I'm tired, I check my twitter feed. Seeing doctors from all over the country come to support Wuhan, I gained the motivation to study again. On the Internet, more and more people pay attention to the doctor's treatment, speak up for them, I also like to see fire.
In the future, I want to be part of the doctor community.
